1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
https://slama.dev/comeback/

2
00:00:10,450 --> 00:00:12,450
You're only now bringing the sign in front of the entrance?

3
00:00:12,830 --> 00:00:13,350
No.

4
00:00:14,450 --> 00:00:16,650
Right, it's time to close up now.

5
00:00:16,950 --> 00:00:17,650
Yeah, I'm carrying it inside.

6
00:00:23,950 --> 00:00:25,950
You'll never guess what happened to me today.

7
00:00:26,040 --> 00:00:26,560
No.

8
00:00:27,350 --> 00:00:28,650
At least try.

9
00:00:31,850 --> 00:00:36,850
You weren't by any chance holed up across the street in the carpet store all afternoon, spying on whether I opened on time, were you?

10
00:00:38,760 --> 00:00:39,280
No.

11
00:00:40,750 --> 00:00:41,550
Well then I don't care.

12
00:00:41,850 --> 00:00:45,090
Wait, you don't care that I was invited to our school for a talk?

13
00:00:45,090 --> 00:00:46,790
As a famous alumnus?

14
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:48,040
No.

15
00:01:23,850 --> 00:01:25,050
Ivo, what if I faint?

16
00:01:26,050 --> 00:01:27,150
Why would you faint?

17
00:01:28,450 --> 00:01:29,450
You just stand up and say Mr. President.

18
00:01:30,780 --> 00:01:31,600
He's not president anymore.

19
00:01:31,860 --> 00:01:32,880
Then Mr. Havel.

20
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:33,700
Havel.

21
00:01:35,450 --> 00:01:42,290
My name is Saša Bučková and I'm the only one from this school the principal allowed to ask questions at talks with famous alumni.

22
00:01:42,290 --> 00:01:43,570
Because he's a scaredy-cat.

23
00:01:43,750 --> 00:01:44,250
Ivo.

24
00:01:45,530 --> 00:01:46,030
Yeah.

25
00:01:46,450 --> 00:01:48,070
And then you ask Havel whatever you want?

26
00:01:48,070 --> 00:01:48,850
But what?

27
00:01:49,450 --> 00:01:51,050
God, we'll think of something.

28
00:01:51,060 --> 00:01:52,560
It's all Kropáčková's fault anyway.

29
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:57,550
If she'd worn a bra today, the mayor wouldn't have made that stupid slip of the tongue at the talk and there wouldn't be a scandal.

30
00:02:01,780 --> 00:02:02,260
Lexa!

31
00:02:03,450 --> 00:02:06,050
I need to get online, I promised Kropáček I'd post it.

32
00:02:06,350 --> 00:02:08,140
Lexa, you can't do that.

33
00:02:08,550 --> 00:02:14,050
Well, since I filmed the mayor on my phone saying they're opening a new breast of the metro.

34
00:02:15,350 --> 00:02:16,540
I'm posting that too.

35
00:02:16,750 --> 00:02:17,850
But Lexa!

36
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:18,720
What?

37
00:02:20,050 --> 00:02:21,650
You still owe me something.

38
00:02:23,150 --> 00:02:24,450
A bet's a bet.

39
00:02:25,450 --> 00:02:26,750
Who could've known?

40
00:02:27,550 --> 00:02:30,750
Me, Saša, and about 10 million others.

41
00:02:30,750 --> 00:02:31,430
Really?

42
00:02:37,850 --> 00:02:39,350
Duck or boulder?

43
00:02:40,350 --> 00:02:40,950
Duck.

44
00:02:41,950 --> 00:02:43,050
Duck is better.

45
00:02:51,650 --> 00:02:52,350
I can't hear anything.

46
00:02:53,750 --> 00:02:59,550
Now sad duck.

47
00:02:59,750 --> 00:03:01,230
Hey, why is the duck sad?

48
00:03:02,050 --> 00:03:03,250
Next time then.

49
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:05,850
Next time I'll win and you'll show me your boobs.

50
00:03:11,950 --> 00:03:13,750
Ivo, what if he wins someday?

51
00:03:15,050 --> 00:03:21,250
A person who bets that nobody can be mayor because the mayor is a cheese will never see my boobs.

52
00:03:33,150 --> 00:03:34,250
Good afternoon.

53
00:03:34,650 --> 00:03:40,550
I'm sorry, but the sleazebag who drove my taxi was delayed with his mistress and picked me up late.

54
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:43,350
He discussed that with you?

55
00:03:43,450 --> 00:03:45,250
He didn't have to, it was obvious.

56
00:03:45,950 --> 00:03:50,150
Marcelka, just because you suspect infidelity doesn't mean all men are the same.

57
00:03:50,420 --> 00:03:53,780
He had an expensive shirt with a hand-embroidered monogram from his wife.

58
00:03:53,780 --> 00:03:58,800
And yet he smelled of cheap glycerin soap, the kind they use in disreputable hotels.

59
00:03:59,350 --> 00:04:01,950
Well, maybe they're saving on soap at home?

60
00:04:03,050 --> 00:04:08,750
Tomáš, such an elegant monogram could not have been embroidered by fingers cracked from glycerin soap.

61
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:13,250
What's the name of the course you took?

62
00:04:13,650 --> 00:04:16,650
Convict Your Husband of Infidelity Using the Deductive Method.

63
00:04:18,350 --> 00:04:19,260
Hats off.

64
00:04:19,450 --> 00:04:21,050
And all that after just the first lesson.

65
00:04:22,950 --> 00:04:25,120
It wasn't that hard, really.

66
00:04:25,350 --> 00:04:28,550
On the way he called her saying he forgot his underwear at the hotel.

67
00:04:29,250 --> 00:04:32,950
Then I'd rather not ask if you can guess what happened to me today.

68
00:04:33,250 --> 00:04:35,050
You mean the talk at the school?

69
00:04:37,150 --> 00:04:38,350
How did you guess?

70
00:04:38,620 --> 00:04:40,660
There's an invitation for Pavel Hornák lying here.

71
00:04:40,660 --> 00:04:43,650
His name is crossed out with a marker and yours is written above it.

72
00:04:45,150 --> 00:04:46,650
Well, Pavel didn't have time.

73
00:04:47,450 --> 00:04:49,160
But you should buy a new jacket for it.

74
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:50,240
You have a hole in your pocket.

75
00:04:50,540 --> 00:04:51,060
What?

76
00:04:52,150 --> 00:04:54,450
Down at the hem I can see the outlines of small coins.

77
00:04:54,750 --> 00:05:00,450
And now excuse me, I took the scoundrel's business card and there's even a home number.

78
00:05:01,250 --> 00:05:02,850
Poor wife of his.

79
00:05:04,450 --> 00:05:08,050
Have you already talked to Ozzák about not opening this afternoon?

80
00:05:08,950 --> 00:05:09,930
What do you mean didn't open?

81
00:05:09,930 --> 00:05:10,470
It rained.

82
00:05:11,250 --> 00:05:14,550
So the spot where the sign usually stands should be dry.

83
00:05:17,430 --> 00:05:18,250
Hello.

84
00:05:18,250 --> 00:05:20,170
He just said that...

85
00:05:20,650 --> 00:05:22,010
Ozzák!

86
00:05:22,010 --> 00:05:22,650
Wait.

87
00:05:24,050 --> 00:05:26,050
He just left, he probably heard us.

88
00:05:26,110 --> 00:05:26,890
He didn't leave.

89
00:05:26,970 --> 00:05:28,390
I sent him to clean the storage room.

90
00:05:30,550 --> 00:05:34,650
You probably didn't feel the draft typical of opening the window to the light well.

91
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:36,800
I'm sorry, excuse me.

92
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:39,240
I'm doing a public opinion survey.

93
00:05:39,460 --> 00:05:41,200
What kind of soap do you use at home?

94
00:05:41,540 --> 00:05:42,700
He's at Simona's!

95
00:05:43,620 --> 00:05:45,220
I know that even without you.

96
00:05:47,950 --> 00:05:49,550
Exclusively olive?

97
00:05:49,790 --> 00:05:51,130
I thought so.

98
00:05:51,130 --> 00:05:56,450
Then I have some interesting information for you.

99
00:06:09,850 --> 00:06:10,650
Ozzák!

100
00:06:12,150 --> 00:06:13,250
Ozzák's not here.

101
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:16,010
That's weird, he's always here.

102
00:06:16,010 --> 00:06:16,410
Not today.

103
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:19,960
You're not even going to ask me if I want something?

104
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:20,220
No.

105
00:06:22,050 --> 00:06:23,650
But I might want something.

106
00:06:24,150 --> 00:06:26,440
My leaky memory, I saw Ozzák.

107
00:06:26,650 --> 00:06:29,150
He said he overslept opening time and went home to apologize to you.

108
00:06:29,350 --> 00:06:30,050
Apologize?

109
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:30,920
He's got plenty to apologize for.

110
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:33,150
Go see him then, so he doesn't suffer too long.

111
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:34,180
You know what?

112
00:06:35,150 --> 00:06:36,250
Fine, let him stew.

113
00:06:36,750 --> 00:06:38,850
He's probably stewing already.

114
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:41,350
And I feel like celebrating.

115
00:06:41,650 --> 00:06:42,850
Bet you can't guess, right?

116
00:06:43,010 --> 00:06:44,030
The talk at the school?

117
00:06:46,050 --> 00:06:46,680
How do you know?

118
00:06:46,850 --> 00:06:48,550
Just knock one back and go see him.

119
00:06:51,850 --> 00:06:53,650
So you're saying he went home?

120
00:06:54,050 --> 00:06:55,050
Oh damn.

121
00:06:55,250 --> 00:06:58,750
Ozzák never leaves an unfinished beer.

122
00:07:03,550 --> 00:07:06,650
So it's probably there, look, under that tarp.

123
00:07:07,050 --> 00:07:08,450
But he wants to apologize.

124
00:07:11,150 --> 00:07:12,050
Let him stew.

125
00:07:23,550 --> 00:07:24,060
Hi.

126
00:07:24,650 --> 00:07:25,550
About time.

127
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:32,450
Ah, dumpling soup.

128
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:33,400
Where's Ozzák?

129
00:07:34,050 --> 00:07:35,150
I have a dumpling for him.

130
00:07:38,350 --> 00:07:39,650
He's cleaning the storage room.

131
00:07:40,050 --> 00:07:42,090
Just when for once it didn't fall apart on me.

132
00:07:42,450 --> 00:07:44,750
So, Ivuška, bet you can't guess.

133
00:07:45,250 --> 00:07:46,650
What happened to me today?

134
00:07:47,050 --> 00:07:48,350
The talk at the school?

135
00:07:49,550 --> 00:07:50,750
How do you know?

136
00:07:51,350 --> 00:07:52,350
The principal called.

137
00:07:53,140 --> 00:07:53,740
Oh.

138
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:55,950
Did he want anything else from me?

139
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:56,880
Nothing from you.

140
00:07:57,650 --> 00:08:02,630
But he asked me to make sure you don't wear that horrible old jacket you wore to school today.

141
00:08:03,750 --> 00:08:05,130
He can't be serious.

142
00:08:05,450 --> 00:08:06,750
That's what I told him too.

143
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:10,550
Ivuška, you shouldn't talk to the principal like that.

144
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:13,950
Although it's nice that you stood up for me.

145
00:08:14,250 --> 00:08:15,650
Who was standing up for you?

146
00:08:15,950 --> 00:08:19,690
I promised him that at the very most I can make sure you buy a new horrible jacket.

147
00:08:21,350 --> 00:08:23,350
What does everyone suddenly have against my jacket?

148
00:08:23,850 --> 00:08:24,790
What do you mean suddenly?

149
00:08:25,050 --> 00:08:27,650
I keep telling you that you look like a grandpa from Vtelno in it.

150
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:30,650
I just look like my dad.

151
00:08:31,050 --> 00:08:32,650
He weighs a hundred kilos and has a mustache.

152
00:08:32,950 --> 00:08:34,450
Only the jacket is the same.

153
00:08:35,250 --> 00:08:37,420
For your information, this is a completely different brown jacket.

154
00:08:37,750 --> 00:08:39,460
But equally horrible.

155
00:08:39,460 --> 00:08:40,760
But it's still fine for now.

156
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:43,050
And the hole in the pocket can be sewn up.

157
00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:44,180
Sewn up.

158
00:08:44,180 --> 00:08:47,940
But I don't want to buy a new jacket yet.

159
00:08:48,250 --> 00:08:49,140
I know.

160
00:08:49,250 --> 00:08:49,950
Good.

161
00:08:50,250 --> 00:08:51,950
Because you always buy the same one.

162
00:08:53,450 --> 00:08:54,450
Ivo, don't annoy me.

163
00:08:54,550 --> 00:08:57,180
As if this were exactly the same as the last one.

164
00:08:57,180 --> 00:08:57,840
Identical.

165
00:08:59,950 --> 00:09:03,050
I don't need to get up and look for the old one.

166
00:09:03,650 --> 00:09:04,540
You can stay seated.

167
00:09:04,850 --> 00:09:05,750
It's right here with us.

168
00:09:06,650 --> 00:09:08,650
Saša made an oven mitt out of it.

169
00:09:11,450 --> 00:09:12,750
But it was still fine.

170
00:09:22,950 --> 00:09:24,070
Look, just admit it.

171
00:09:24,550 --> 00:09:26,590
You're going to keep buying brown jackets till you die.

172
00:09:26,750 --> 00:09:27,550
Excuse me, I can change.

173
00:09:28,890 --> 00:09:29,570
Change the jacket.

174
00:09:30,250 --> 00:09:33,350
Fine, when I go buy a new jacket, it'll be different.

175
00:09:36,350 --> 00:09:38,250
Actually it's a slightly different color.

176
00:09:38,990 --> 00:09:39,510
Really?

177
00:09:40,550 --> 00:09:41,290
Look, see?

178
00:09:41,650 --> 00:09:43,250
There are these white threads here.

179
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:45,060
Those are noodles.

180
00:09:46,550 --> 00:09:47,050
Don't you dare.

181
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:11,750
What a mess, Mamba, don't do this to me.

182
00:10:11,780 --> 00:10:12,640
Do what?

183
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:14,050
Go to the pub.

184
00:10:14,650 --> 00:10:16,190
Did I say anything?

185
00:10:16,290 --> 00:10:17,170
Simple deduction.

186
00:10:17,290 --> 00:10:17,710
What?

187
00:10:18,650 --> 00:10:23,210
Using deduction I can read even your most secret thoughts from your facial expressions and eye movements.

188
00:10:23,210 --> 00:10:24,330
I'd like to see that.

189
00:10:24,470 --> 00:10:26,430
Any beginner could see through you.

190
00:10:27,750 --> 00:10:29,550
Nevertheless, as practice.

191
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:36,360
So, after you dug around in your ear, which was a sign that you caught my attention, your eyes fixed on the door.

192
00:10:36,540 --> 00:10:39,820
From your facial expression I concluded that you started thinking.

193
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:43,260
You thought it was so nice outside that maybe the beer gardens were open.

194
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:46,440
Then you glanced at the fire extinguisher and swallowed.

195
00:10:46,820 --> 00:10:48,620
You realized how thirsty you were.

196
00:10:49,050 --> 00:10:56,550
And when you then looked at that poster with the tongue sticking out, you thought how easy it would be to blow this off and head to a pub.

197
00:10:57,350 --> 00:10:58,150
Was I right?

198
00:10:58,910 --> 00:10:59,250
No!

199
00:11:02,150 --> 00:11:03,650
Why were you looking around so much then?

200
00:11:05,550 --> 00:11:06,550
There was a fly buzzing around.

201
00:11:11,050 --> 00:11:12,550
But since you bring it up...

202
00:11:20,140 --> 00:11:20,980
Where are you going?

203
00:11:22,150 --> 00:11:23,450
To clean the storage room.

204
00:11:23,610 --> 00:11:25,390
You didn't clean it yesterday?

205
00:11:25,550 --> 00:11:26,670
Wasn't in the mood!

206
00:11:28,040 --> 00:11:29,500
And why do you have a fly swatter?

207
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:31,160
Ask Mamba, she knows everything!

208
00:11:33,890 --> 00:11:34,450
Marcelka?

209
00:11:34,450 --> 00:11:35,970
Good morning, Tomáš.

210
00:11:35,970 --> 00:11:37,440
So what about the jacket?

211
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:40,220
I arranged with Iva that she'll sew up the hole.

212
00:11:40,450 --> 00:11:43,450
You're going before students in an unfashionable patched-up jacket?

213
00:11:43,950 --> 00:11:45,140
What do you mean unfashionable?

214
00:11:45,450 --> 00:11:47,450
I bought it in the young fashion department.

215
00:11:47,950 --> 00:11:49,850
Have you ever seen an old fashion department?

216
00:11:49,850 --> 00:11:50,210
No.

217
00:11:50,430 --> 00:11:52,550
You really don't understand marketing.

218
00:11:52,550 --> 00:11:54,950
The young fashion department is fashion for old people.

219
00:11:56,050 --> 00:11:57,250
Isn't that confusing?

220
00:11:58,050 --> 00:12:01,610
If any department were called old fashion, nobody would go there.

221
00:12:01,610 --> 00:12:02,810
Why not?

222
00:12:02,810 --> 00:12:04,650
Because they'd feel old.

223
00:12:04,850 --> 00:12:05,550
Well then.

224
00:12:07,150 --> 00:12:09,650
So what is fashion for actually young people called?

225
00:12:10,050 --> 00:12:11,150
Freedom on Skate.

226
00:12:13,450 --> 00:12:15,350
I don't feel old in it.

227
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:27,550
Bro, what the heck is going on here?

228
00:12:28,350 --> 00:12:30,250
There always used to be a Jednota here.

229
00:12:39,250 --> 00:12:40,250
Fine, alright.

230
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:43,250
See, the principal will be happy.

231
00:12:44,950 --> 00:12:46,150
He told you too?

232
00:12:46,550 --> 00:12:48,750
We also have basics of espionage.

233
00:12:49,730 --> 00:12:51,210
I'll get to it later, Marcelka.

234
00:12:51,390 --> 00:12:53,210
Don't be angry, but I need to learn this somehow.

235
00:12:53,310 --> 00:12:54,890
Zoran is no beginner.

236
00:12:55,390 --> 00:12:58,550
Surely one brown hair on a shirt isn't proof of infidelity.

237
00:12:58,770 --> 00:13:01,190
In the end it wasn't a hair, it was horsehair.

238
00:13:01,820 --> 00:13:02,440
Well, there you go.

239
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:05,050
That's even worse, Zoran hates horses.

240
00:13:05,750 --> 00:13:07,520
Well, maybe he brushed against one somewhere.

241
00:13:08,050 --> 00:13:10,980
In his pocket he had a tissue with a horse motif on it.

242
00:13:11,550 --> 00:13:13,560
Well, maybe he couldn't find a different one.

243
00:13:13,850 --> 00:13:15,550
There were traces of a woman's tears on it.

244
00:13:16,350 --> 00:13:17,500
It's probably eating at her too.

245
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:18,200
That hussy.

246
00:13:22,180 --> 00:13:22,780
Sorry.

247
00:13:24,550 --> 00:13:29,750
Zoran always promised he'd go horseback riding with me.

248
00:13:31,150 --> 00:13:31,750
Why are you barging in?

249
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:35,260
I'm the one cleaning here.

250
00:13:41,740 --> 00:13:42,580
Is it ready?

251
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:43,080
Just a moment.

252
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:47,900
A boulder doesn't talk, a boulder is a rock.

253
00:13:48,380 --> 00:13:49,720
Ivo, just leave him alone.

254
00:13:50,020 --> 00:13:51,240
Do you feel sorry for him?

255
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:55,050
No, but it makes me nervous that he's looking over my shoulder.

256
00:13:56,950 --> 00:13:58,550
Boulder, go away.

257
00:14:00,260 --> 00:14:01,500
I'm not betting anymore.

258
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:03,250
You won't last.

259
00:14:03,770 --> 00:14:05,930
Ivo, I can't handle it, I'll definitely faint.

260
00:14:06,110 --> 00:14:07,350
You'll see, you'll manage.

261
00:14:07,610 --> 00:14:08,170
She won't.

262
00:14:10,150 --> 00:14:12,150
Don't you get it, she will.

263
00:14:12,710 --> 00:14:13,430
Sit down.

264
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:18,540
Are you scared?

265
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:19,840
No.

266
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:21,000
Then.

267
00:14:24,150 --> 00:14:25,050
Saša, I'm sorry.

268
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:26,560
I can't handle it.

269
00:14:27,460 --> 00:14:28,460
You will, don't worry.

270
00:14:29,180 --> 00:14:29,820
You think?

271
00:14:29,820 --> 00:14:33,550
She doesn't think so, otherwise she wouldn't be sitting down.

272
00:14:34,780 --> 00:14:35,420
Fine.

273
00:14:36,650 --> 00:14:38,080
Ivo, don't do it, I can't handle it.

274
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:38,600
You will.

275
00:14:40,450 --> 00:14:41,150
Yeah, I get to see boobs.

276
00:14:46,450 --> 00:14:47,650
I believe you.

277
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:50,800
Now I definitely can't handle it.

278
00:14:52,280 --> 00:14:56,550
Hi, Dad.

279
00:14:56,920 --> 00:14:58,960
Hey, that new jacket looks good on you.

280
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:00,660
Ivo, don't be sarcastic.

281
00:15:01,450 --> 00:15:03,920
And I'm glad you didn't come with me, you'd just make me nervous.

282
00:15:04,150 --> 00:15:06,340
But shopping with Simča was different.

283
00:15:07,650 --> 00:15:10,400
She found the store, picked the size, I didn't even have to go to the register.

284
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:11,300
She took care of everything.

285
00:15:12,050 --> 00:15:15,760
Prices went up since the last jacket, but at least I'll look presentable.

286
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:16,540
Let's see.

287
00:15:16,950 --> 00:15:19,480
I'll run upstairs and bring it to you nicely unwrapped.

288
00:15:20,050 --> 00:15:20,650
Why?

289
00:15:21,050 --> 00:15:23,170
So wrapping paper doesn't pile up here.

290
00:15:23,470 --> 00:15:24,730
They are actually piling up here.

291
00:15:24,830 --> 00:15:26,370
They iron them and save them for Christmas.

292
00:15:27,390 --> 00:15:28,650
Saša will iron them for you.

293
00:15:28,750 --> 00:15:29,170
May I?

294
00:15:29,370 --> 00:15:29,910
No!

295
00:15:30,950 --> 00:15:32,850
You've done quite enough.

296
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:39,770
The saleswoman said hazelnut goes best with my complexion.

297
00:15:39,770 --> 00:15:40,390
So brown.

298
00:15:42,290 --> 00:15:42,850
No!

299
00:15:43,550 --> 00:15:45,450
Hazelnut!

300
00:15:56,750 --> 00:15:59,810
Well, under those fluorescent lights in the store it looked a bit different.

301
00:16:00,350 --> 00:16:01,150
Try it on, let's see the revolution.

302
00:16:02,390 --> 00:16:03,110
I'll help you.

303
00:16:03,250 --> 00:16:04,390
No, please don't!

304
00:16:05,150 --> 00:16:07,110
I'm not having a woman help me into my jacket.

305
00:16:07,110 --> 00:16:17,370
And now the new one.

306
00:16:18,650 --> 00:16:19,650
Stop it!

307
00:16:20,150 --> 00:16:23,450
Maybe it's not a huge change, but at least I won't have holes in my pockets.

308
00:16:32,550 --> 00:16:33,300
That's Simona.

309
00:16:33,300 --> 00:16:48,960
What happened?

310
00:16:51,150 --> 00:16:51,970
Forgive her, Tomáš.

311
00:16:52,350 --> 00:16:54,950
She just found out her husband is cheating on her too.

312
00:16:56,250 --> 00:16:57,250
You have a new jacket.

313
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:57,760
What?

314
00:16:58,220 --> 00:16:59,040
You noticed?

315
00:16:59,750 --> 00:17:01,350
And I'm surely the only one.

316
00:17:02,250 --> 00:17:03,010
How do you know?

317
00:17:03,250 --> 00:17:07,450
Very few people notice at first glance four buttons on the sleeve instead of three.

318
00:17:10,350 --> 00:17:11,650
And now it's a different color.

319
00:17:11,750 --> 00:17:13,780
This is hazelnut shade.

320
00:17:13,780 --> 00:17:15,040
The old one was caramel.

321
00:17:15,950 --> 00:17:18,350
And this is supposed to be the change you promised Iva?

322
00:17:18,750 --> 00:17:20,840
I didn't promise Iva anything.

323
00:17:20,840 --> 00:17:21,140
No?

324
00:17:24,550 --> 00:17:26,610
Wednesday 7:36 PM.

325
00:17:26,610 --> 00:17:29,030
Tomáš: Excuse me, I can change.

326
00:17:29,070 --> 00:17:30,050
Iva: Change the jacket.

327
00:17:30,150 --> 00:17:33,590
Tomáš: Fine, when I buy a new jacket, it'll be different.

328
00:17:36,350 --> 00:17:40,850
Marcelka, I'm asking you to stop practicing on our family.

329
00:17:41,360 --> 00:17:44,040
Sitting in a parked car outside our building at night?

330
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:50,150
Ozzák says you took his fingerprints and now you've installed listening devices in our apartment?

331
00:17:51,330 --> 00:17:53,490
No bugs, I listened through the door.

332
00:17:54,030 --> 00:17:55,710
They teach us classical methods too.

333
00:17:55,970 --> 00:17:57,210
Just stop it.

334
00:17:57,210 --> 00:18:00,250
I have nothing to be ashamed of, but it's unpleasant.

335
00:18:00,670 --> 00:18:01,170
You don't?

336
00:18:01,890 --> 00:18:02,830
What do you mean?

337
00:18:03,110 --> 00:18:04,790
I didn't think you were like that too.

338
00:18:05,830 --> 00:18:06,330
Like what?

339
00:18:06,330 --> 00:18:08,150
The same as everyone else.

340
00:18:08,750 --> 00:18:12,580
You make a promise, sweet talk, and then you just throw it all away.

341
00:18:12,580 --> 00:18:14,700
And the poor woman cries all night.

342
00:18:14,900 --> 00:18:16,840
But I didn't promise anything.

343
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:19,840
I just said I'd buy a different jacket.

344
00:18:19,840 --> 00:18:20,680
But you didn't.

345
00:18:22,700 --> 00:18:23,260
Wait.

346
00:18:24,450 --> 00:18:25,750
Iva cries at night?

347
00:18:26,850 --> 00:18:28,250
You haven't understood anything.

348
00:18:28,580 --> 00:18:29,140
No.

349
00:18:33,150 --> 00:18:34,530
So you don't like the jacket either?

350
00:18:34,530 --> 00:18:34,770
No!

351
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:43,350
I'll kill him!

352
00:18:44,650 --> 00:18:45,950
I'm going to throw up.

353
00:18:46,050 --> 00:18:48,220
I'll throw up when Lexa looks at me.

354
00:18:48,220 --> 00:18:49,060
Ivo, I'm sorry.

355
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:50,860
It's too late for apologies.

356
00:18:50,860 --> 00:18:53,020
You should've asked a question instead of correcting him.

357
00:18:53,120 --> 00:18:54,220
But he made a mistake.

358
00:18:54,580 --> 00:18:55,680
You don't correct presidents.

359
00:18:55,740 --> 00:18:56,540
He's not president anymore.

360
00:18:57,530 --> 00:18:58,690
Don't correct me either.

361
00:18:58,870 --> 00:18:59,590
Sorry, Ivo.

362
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:03,200
This is the worst day of my life.

363
00:19:03,340 --> 00:19:04,160
Mine too.

364
00:19:04,260 --> 00:19:05,400
Except you brought it on yourself.

365
00:19:05,760 --> 00:19:08,180
But he said the Dnieper is longer than the Volga.

366
00:19:08,340 --> 00:19:08,880
So what?

367
00:19:09,620 --> 00:19:10,580
The Volga is longer.

368
00:19:12,650 --> 00:19:14,200
Then it's good you told him.

369
00:19:14,550 --> 00:19:15,550
Now he knows.

370
00:19:15,750 --> 00:19:17,450
Lexa is getting his camera ready.

371
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:21,340
For God's sake, why do you correct presidents if you then crash to the ground?

372
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:23,660
He's not president anymore and that's not why I fainted.

373
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:24,360
Then why?

374
00:19:24,480 --> 00:19:29,020
Because I said that it's not true that the Dnieper is longer than the Volga, do you get it?

375
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:29,440
No.

376
00:19:30,650 --> 00:19:32,850
I said "ass" in front of the president.

377
00:19:40,350 --> 00:19:41,290
And he's not president anymore.

378
00:19:41,450 --> 00:19:42,550
I know.

379
00:19:50,350 --> 00:19:51,250
Thanks, sis.

380
00:19:52,050 --> 00:19:52,750
Let's see.

381
00:19:54,150 --> 00:19:55,350
Ivo, I'm sorry.

382
00:19:56,150 --> 00:19:57,340
Forget about the camera.

383
00:19:57,340 --> 00:19:58,630
It's cool.

384
00:20:02,250 --> 00:20:03,350
Don't you want to wait a bit?

385
00:20:03,360 --> 00:20:03,700
No.

386
00:20:05,150 --> 00:20:06,130
Maybe until the evening?

387
00:20:06,130 --> 00:20:06,270
No.

388
00:20:07,450 --> 00:20:08,750
But they're bigger in the evening.

389
00:20:12,650 --> 00:20:14,750
Right, sure thing.

390
00:20:16,750 --> 00:20:17,750
Fine, I'll see tonight.

391
00:20:18,950 --> 00:20:20,850
Alright, I'll show you tonight.

392
00:20:20,850 --> 00:20:21,350
Awesome.

393
00:20:22,750 --> 00:20:25,050
So I'll put the Havel video online in the meantime.

394
00:20:25,950 --> 00:20:28,290
Kropáčková ended up asking a question after all.

395
00:20:28,750 --> 00:20:31,150
Of course, as soon as you two were gone.

396
00:20:31,150 --> 00:20:32,550
But what did she ask?

397
00:20:33,350 --> 00:20:34,250
Who cares?

398
00:20:48,150 --> 00:20:50,550
I'm leaving.

399
00:21:00,150 --> 00:21:01,550
Don't go anywhere.

400
00:21:02,320 --> 00:21:04,160
Marcelka is in some strange mood today.

401
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:06,950
I have a feeling she wants to confront Zoran with her accusation.

402
00:21:07,750 --> 00:21:09,250
Then I'll have one more, son.

403
00:21:09,520 --> 00:21:10,000
A shot.

404
00:21:11,060 --> 00:21:12,220
That wasn't very nice.

405
00:21:12,420 --> 00:21:13,240
Don't provoke me.

406
00:21:13,380 --> 00:21:14,420
You still owe me one.

407
00:21:14,420 --> 00:21:18,650
Come on, we got you such a nice jacket, you look so dapper in it.

408
00:21:19,450 --> 00:21:21,750
Hell, I'm wearing the old one.

409
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:26,100
Sorry, the brown threw me off.

410
00:21:26,550 --> 00:21:29,550
What the hell is so weird about me simply liking brown jackets?

411
00:21:29,650 --> 00:21:31,950
Of course, Mr. Brown has to wear brown.

412
00:21:34,260 --> 00:21:34,780
What?

413
00:21:36,150 --> 00:21:39,240
Mr. Brown, that's what everyone called you all through high school.

414
00:21:43,450 --> 00:21:47,470
Oh for God's sake, I wasn't even wearing anything brown back then.

415
00:21:47,650 --> 00:21:49,110
What about that brown jacket?

416
00:21:49,350 --> 00:21:51,350
That was dark beige.

417
00:21:51,950 --> 00:21:54,750
Well true, but Mr. Dark Beige wouldn't have the same ring to it.

418
00:21:56,950 --> 00:21:58,220
So Mr. Brown, huh?

419
00:21:58,220 --> 00:21:59,060
It's shorter.

420
00:22:01,050 --> 00:22:04,550
I'll show you, I'll show you all!

421
00:22:04,950 --> 00:22:06,490
Leave that shot here!

422
00:22:06,490 --> 00:22:09,010
He's in a strange mood too.

423
00:22:09,230 --> 00:22:10,510
But I've got something perfectly harmless for you.

424
00:22:11,450 --> 00:22:15,050
Simona, not a word about this business in front of her.

425
00:22:15,550 --> 00:22:16,650
I'd never hear the end of it.

426
00:22:20,550 --> 00:22:25,650
Sorry to barge in like this, but I have an important meeting ahead and I need some liquid courage.

427
00:22:32,750 --> 00:22:34,440
And you're always near the booze.

428
00:22:41,250 --> 00:22:42,060
What a day.

429
00:22:49,250 --> 00:22:50,050
Fine, I'm showing.

430
00:22:51,750 --> 00:22:53,600
I thought the lights would be on.

431
00:22:53,850 --> 00:22:54,950
Nobody said that.

432
00:22:55,560 --> 00:22:56,020
Damn.

433
00:22:59,050 --> 00:23:00,850
Why are the lights off?

434
00:23:05,480 --> 00:23:06,900
You haven't undressed!

435
00:23:08,330 --> 00:23:08,970
Ivo?

436
00:23:09,910 --> 00:23:10,550
Dad?

437
00:23:12,350 --> 00:23:13,850
Well, Lexa?

438
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:16,640
Did you already buy Ivo a skateboard?

439
00:23:33,660 --> 00:23:34,300
Marcelka?

440
00:23:34,620 --> 00:23:35,320
Am I intruding?

441
00:23:35,750 --> 00:23:37,950
No, no, no, come on in.

442
00:23:40,950 --> 00:23:41,870
Is something going on?

443
00:23:42,050 --> 00:23:43,450
It is, Tomáš, it is.

444
00:23:43,950 --> 00:23:46,650
Zoran is buying me a horse, a beautiful brown one.

445
00:23:46,710 --> 00:23:48,590
Oh, that's nice.

446
00:23:48,910 --> 00:23:50,250
He's trying to make it up to you.

447
00:23:50,430 --> 00:23:52,930
There's nothing to make up for, he didn't do anything wrong, he explained everything.

448
00:23:53,750 --> 00:23:54,610
Even the handkerchief?

449
00:23:54,610 --> 00:23:54,730
Yes.

450
00:23:55,550 --> 00:23:58,570
Those tears belonged to the young lady selling the pony.

451
00:23:58,570 --> 00:24:00,470
She didn't want to part with him, poor thing.

452
00:24:00,510 --> 00:24:02,630
Zoran had to talk her into it for many evenings.

453
00:24:04,650 --> 00:24:06,500
I'm so happy.

454
00:24:07,050 --> 00:24:11,030
And that new jacket really suits you today.

455
00:24:11,450 --> 00:24:12,390
This is the old one.

456
00:24:12,850 --> 00:24:13,550
Well, the buttons.

457
00:24:14,550 --> 00:24:15,850
To hell with the buttons.

458
00:24:16,230 --> 00:24:17,370
You look great.

459
00:24:17,450 --> 00:24:18,730
Yeah, thanks.

460
00:24:19,550 --> 00:24:22,730
I exchanged the new one for some youthful clothing, but I won't wear it.

461
00:24:22,930 --> 00:24:23,850
It's not my style.

462
00:24:24,090 --> 00:24:24,830
That's alright.

463
00:24:25,530 --> 00:24:27,330
I was such a fool.

464
00:24:27,330 --> 00:24:32,150
I thought I could examine love using scientific methods.

465
00:24:32,450 --> 00:24:37,150
I was deducing and missed the flight of the fly.

466
00:24:39,350 --> 00:24:42,330
Marcelka, I haven't understood you much lately.

467
00:24:42,650 --> 00:24:46,250
It doesn't matter, but you look great.

468
00:24:46,520 --> 00:24:47,740
Well, I'm off.

469
00:24:47,740 --> 00:24:51,700
Zoran popped over to Hotel Kopule to sign the contract with the young lady.

470
00:24:51,700 --> 00:24:53,380
But he should be done by now.

471
00:24:54,350 --> 00:24:58,450
And then we're going for a ride on Tomík.

472
00:24:58,540 --> 00:24:59,240
On who?

473
00:24:59,460 --> 00:25:00,600
The brown horse.

474
00:25:00,740 --> 00:25:02,060
I gave him that name.

475
00:25:03,050 --> 00:25:04,750
I have no idea where I got it from.

476
00:25:05,200 --> 00:25:06,130
Bye then.

477
00:25:17,650 --> 00:25:19,950
It's not so bad yet.

478
00:25:20,950 --> 00:25:23,560
Hopefully you won't have to be ashamed of me at the talk.

479
00:25:23,850 --> 00:25:25,500
Never mind me, watch out for Kropáčková.

480
00:25:25,750 --> 00:25:27,450
So you won't be the one who's embarrassed.

481
00:25:27,850 --> 00:25:29,850
You'll see, it'll turn out fine.

482
00:25:30,950 --> 00:25:31,850
I won't see.

483
00:25:32,340 --> 00:25:32,940
What?

484
00:25:33,770 --> 00:25:36,430
The principal let me sort recycling in the yard instead of attending the talk.

485
00:25:37,750 --> 00:25:39,290
Ivo, that's awful.

486
00:25:39,950 --> 00:25:40,530
Why?

487
00:25:40,850 --> 00:25:42,550
At least I'll do something for the planet, right?

488
00:25:44,550 --> 00:25:47,150
So, bro, it's just us two going.

489
00:25:49,450 --> 00:25:51,550
Sorry, bro, I'm in the mood to clean.

490
00:25:59,350 --> 00:26:00,750
Good day, Mr. Principal.

491
00:26:01,450 --> 00:26:03,550
Ah, Mr. Pacovský.

492
00:26:03,710 --> 00:26:06,090
I have to prepare you for something.

493
00:26:06,830 --> 00:26:07,810
A delicate matter.

494
00:26:11,350 --> 00:26:16,950
I was telling you not to wear that jacket.

495
00:26:18,450 --> 00:26:19,850
We'll look like twins.

496
00:26:20,970 --> 00:26:22,810
Well, they're not exactly the same.

497
00:26:22,830 --> 00:26:24,630
Let's go, let's go.

498
00:26:28,250 --> 00:26:30,550
So I couldn't convince that Hornák after all.
